%h3 First, you'll need to create a github token
%p
  Visit
  = link_to 'Generate a Github access token', 'https://github.com/settings/tokens/new?scope=repo,user:email', target: '_blank'

= form_for user, url: user_path, method: :put, html: { class: 'update-github-token' } do |f|
  %strong
    = f.label :github_access_token, 'Github Token'
  = f.text_field :github_access_token, placeholder: 'Paste your GitHub token here'
  %label.subscribe-flag
    = f.check_box :subscribe, {}, true, false
    Sign up for our newsletter - Get all the latest news, tips & tricks for Panamax
  %p
    %strong Planning on entering the $100,000+ Panamax App Template Challenge 2014?
    %br/
    First, fork the
    = link_to "Panamax Contest Templates", "https://github.com/CenturyLinkLabs/panamax-contest-templates"
    repository to your personal Github Account, and then save your template there.
    = link_to "Learn more about the contest & the submission process.", "http://panamax.io/contest"
  = f.button 'Save Token', class: 'button-positive'
